The paper deals with network design problems on directed graphs, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), network economics (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of submodular functions and approximation algorithms further suggests a connection to these subfields.
